questions.scenario:
Bug Hunter: You are reviewing code for a high-throughput gateway migrated to Java 21. Users report that under heavy load, the application becomes unresponsive and CPU usage spikes, even though Virtual Threads are used. You find the following snippet:

java
public void processRequest(Request req) {
    Thread.startVirtualThread(() -> {
        synchronized (this.lock) {
            String metadata = cache.get(req.id());
            if (metadata == null) {
                metadata = dbClient.fetchBlocking(req.id()); // JDBC call
                cache.put(req.id(), metadata);
            }
        }
    });
}
